{"parse":{"title":"Racial Justice Sunday","pageid":2662024,"revid":825085409,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox vevent\" style=\"width:22em\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" class=\"hd\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;background-color: transparent\">Racial Justice Sunday</th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Date</th><td>\nSecond Sunday in February</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Frequency</th><td>\nAnnual</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:St_P_9-11-05.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/c/c6/St_P_9-11-05.jpg/220px-St_P_9-11-05.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"143\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/c/c6/St_P_9-11-05.jpg/330px-St_P_9-11-05.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/c/c6/St_P_9-11-05.jpg/440px-St_P_9-11-05.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"2400\" data-file-height=\"1561\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:St_P_9-11-05.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>At the entrance to <a href=\"/wiki/St_Paul%27s_Cathedral\" title=\"St Paul&#39;s Cathedral\">St Paul's Cathedral</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/London\" title=\"London\">London</a>, featuring banners from <a href=\"/wiki/Peace_and_Progress\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Peace and Progress\">Peace and Progress</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Dale_Farm\" title=\"Dale Farm\">Dale Farm</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Azelle_Rodney\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Azelle Rodney\">Azelle Rodney</a> campaigns.</div></div></div>\n<p><b>Racial Justice Sunday</b> is observed by <a href=\"/wiki/United_Kingdom\" title=\"United Kingdom\">British</a> Christian churches on the second Sunday of February. It began in 1995. On 11 September 2005, special celebrations were held in <a href=\"/wiki/Cardiff\" title=\"Cardiff\">Cardiff</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Glasgow\" title=\"Glasgow\">Glasgow</a>, and <a href=\"/wiki/London\" title=\"London\">London</a> for the tenth anniversary of this day of observance.\n</p><p>The <a href=\"/wiki/Methodist_Church_in_Britain\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Methodist Church in Britain\">Methodist Church in Britain</a> describes Racial Justice Sunday as \"an opportunity for all Christians to join together in:\n</p>\n<ul><li>Reflecting on the importance of racial justice</li>\n<li>Thanksgiving for human diversity</li>\n<li>Prayer for an end to misunderstanding, racism and injustice</li>\n<li>Action that truly makes a difference</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Fundraising\" title=\"Fundraising\">Fundraising</a> for national and local racial justice initiatives.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-Methodist_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Methodist-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<p>Racial Justice Sunday moved from the second Sunday of September to the second Sunday of February, with effect from 2017,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Methodist_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Methodist-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> at the same time as <a href=\"/wiki/Education_Sunday\" title=\"Education Sunday\">Education Sunday</a> was moved to the second Sunday in September because of its more logical connection with the start of the <a href=\"/wiki/School_year\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"School year\">school year</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> In 2018 the day will be marked on 11 February.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Methodist_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Methodist-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Racial_Justice_Sunday&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Methodist-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-Methodist_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Methodist_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Methodist_1-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Methodist Church in Britain, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://methodist.org.uk/prayer-and-worship/methodist-special-sundays/racial-justice-sunday\">Racial Justice Sunday</a>, accessed 29 August 2017</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.cte.org.uk/Groups/234838/Home/Resources/Education_Sunday/Education_Sunday.aspx\">Education Sunday: News re 2016 date change</a>, accessed 21 August 2017</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"/wiki/File:Calendar_icon.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Stub icon\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/dd/Calendar_icon.svg/23px-Calendar_icon.svg.png\" width=\"23\" height=\"30\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/dd/Calendar_icon.svg/35px-Calendar_icon.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/dd/Calendar_icon.svg/47px-Calendar_icon.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"720\" data-file-height=\"920\" /></a></td><td><i>This <a href=\"/wiki/Holiday\" title=\"Holiday\">holiday</a>-related article is a <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Stub\" title=\"Wikipedia:Stub\">stub</a>. You can help Wikipedia by <a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Racial_Justice_Sunday&amp;action=edit\">expanding it</a>.</i><div class=\"plainlinks hlist na